<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25175e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25175e">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25175e"> 175(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hottentot apron</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Zulu wooden pillow is exactly like that used in ancient Egypt, and the Bushmen not only possess a power of drawing and painting which may be thought to be a survival of Egyptian art, but also a peculiar physical conformation (the &ldquo;tablier &Eacute;gyptien,&rdquo; or &ldquo;<mark>Hottentot apron</mark>&rdquo;), which may also connect them with the old race of the Nile delta. <small> Claude R. Conder, <a name="CRRM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CRRM"><cite title="source">The Rise of Man</cite></a> (1908) 55</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Elongated labia (also known as <i>Sinus pudoris</i> or <i>macronympha</i> and albeit nonmedically, as khoikhoi apron or hottentot apron), are a feature of certain Khoisan groups, whose female members develop relatively elongated labia minora, hanging up to four inches outside their vulva when they are standing in an upright position.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c14118l" href="c14all.htm#c14118l">VI.C.14:118(l)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
